<TEXT>
DEPARTMENT of Employment officials had warned ministers that the sale of
four Skillcentres to an organisation which subsequently went into
liquidation would be risky, according to a report published yesterday by the
Commons Public Accounts Committee.
The committee said the ministers had decided to go ahead 'in the light of
their objectives for the privatisation'.
The committee investigated the department's management of the sell-off of 60
Skillcentres. In May 1990 it completed the sale of 51 Skillcentres on terms
which required them to pay the purchasers Pounds 13.6m.
