<HEADLINE>
FT  01 MAY 92 / World News in Brief: Sierra Leone coup claim
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mutinous soldiers said they had ousted Joseph Momoh, Sierra Leone's
president since 1985. The rebels' leader, Lieutenant-Colonel Yaya Kanu,
promised to restore democracy. Momoh fled by helicopter to neighbouring
Guinea.
</TEXT>
