</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CONTINUED demand for blue chips lifted Johannesburg, taking the week's gains
to 2.4 per cent. The overall index rose 24 to 3,453 and the industrial index
was 19 higher at 4,311. The gold index was up 7 at 1,017 on firmer bullion
