Mr Paul Van Zuydam, chairman, said that first quarter sales were encouraging
with volumes up in most parts of the world.
He said that this should have a positive effect on factory overhead recovery
and operating profit.
Earnings per share rose from 13.1p to 13.7p.
A dividend of FFr0.42 is proposed for the year, compared with a total of
FFr0.39 for 1990.
