<HEADLINE>
FT  01 MAY 92 / Technology: Diesel fuel comes clean - Worth Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Water contamination in diesel fuel can cause breakdowns, particularly in
cold weather when the water freezes.
Unlike other diesel additives Aquasolve, a new product marketed by Shurflo,
of Reigate, Surrey, and based on research by the Thermo-Fluids Engineering
Research centre at City University in London, bonds the water to the fuel to
form a solution that burns cleanly with no adverse effects or power loss.
Shurflo also claims the blending helps improve combustion, cleans engines
and reduces emissions. Aquasolve is equally effective treating fuel
contaminated with sea water and prevents bacteriological growth caused when
diesel fuel is stored in tanks. Shurflo: UK, 0737 242282.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
