FT  01 MAY 92 / Liquid assets
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Liquid assets: The Queen Mary II, a steamship used as a bar and restaurant
in London, is for sale at Pounds 2m. The steamship, the last turbine-steamer
on the Clyde, was called the Queen Mary in 1933. Two years later the
shipbuilder was persuaded, by Buckingham Palace it is said, to amend the
name since Cunard wanted to launch the liner of that title.
