<HEADLINE>
FT  01 MAY 92 / World Trade News: Hong Kong airport body to seek loan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SIMON HOLBERTON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Hong Kong authority responsible for building and operating the colony's
new airport has been given provisional authority to borrow HKDollars 23.3bn
(Pounds 1.67bn) to finance the construction of the airport, though it will
take months before it is ready to approach the world's capital markets,
writes Simon Holberton in Hong Kong.
Mrs Anson Chan, a senior Hong Kong official, said the Provisional Airport
Authority's (PAA) capital funding requirement - including interest payments
and fees associated with the borrowings - was HKDollars 38.2bn, in March
1991 prices.
The PAA's finance director said the authority would be seeking the
longest-term financing that was available from the market.
</TEXT>
