power sharing with blacks, ceding the initiative on interim government to a
multi-party forum.
Government negotiator Mr Tertius Delport said Mr de Klerk would put on ice
his own proposals for interim rule while delegates to the Convention for a
Democratic South Africa (Codesa) considered an alternative plan.
