OMV, which has interests in oil refining, gas marketing, chemicals and
plastics, saw increased sales in all sectors. Turnover rose 6.5 per cent to
Sch82.9bn from Sch77.87bn.
The company is making a push into eastern Europe; last year it opened 13
filling stations in Hungary and Czechoslovakia. It has just signed a
contract to open 60 petrol stations in Slovenia and is looking at expansion
into Bavaria and northern Italy.
